targets = dataset.targets
indices = list(range(len(dataset)))

train_indices, temp_indices = train_test_split(indices, test_size=0.3, stratify=targets)
val_indices, test_indices = train_test_split(temp_indices, test_size=0.5, stratify=[targets[i] for i in temp_indices])

train_dataset = Subset(dataset, train_indices)
train_loader = DataLoader(Subset(dataset, train_indices), batch_size=BATCH_SIZE, shuffle=True)
val_dataset = Subset(dataset, val_indices)
val_loader = DataLoader(val_dataset, batch_size=BATCH_SIZE, shuffle=False)
test_dataset = Subset(dataset, test_indices)
test_loader = DataLoader(test_dataset, batch_size=BATCH_SIZE, shuffle=False)

print("Train dataset size:", len(train_dataset))
print("Validation dataset size:", len(val_dataset))
print("Test dataset size:", len(test_dataset))

class RESNET50(nn.Module):
    def __init__(self, num_classes: int) -> None:
        super(RESNET50, self).__init__()
        self.model = models.resnet50(weights=models.ResNet50_Weights.IMAGENET1K_V2)
        self.model.fc = nn.Linear(self.model.fc.in_features, num_classes)
        for param in self.model.parameters():
            param.requires_grad = True

    def forward(self, input):
        return self.model(input)


class RESNET50_ADD_BOTELNECK(nn.Module):
    def __init__(self, num_classes: int) -> None:
        super(RESNET50_ADD_BOTELNECK, self).__init__()
        self.model = models.resnet50(weights=models.ResNet50_Weights.IMAGENET1K_V2)
        for param in self.model.parameters():
            param.requires_grad = False

        self.model.new_block = nn.Sequential(
            nn.Conv2d(in_channels=2048, out_channels=64, kernel_size=1, padding=0),
            nn.BatchNorm2d(num_features=64),
            nn.ReLU(inplace=True),
            nn.Conv2d(in_channels=64, out_channels=64, kernel_size=1, padding=0),
            nn.BatchNorm2d(num_features=64),
            nn.ReLU(inplace=True),
        )
        self.model.fc = nn.Linear(64, num_classes)

        for param in self.model.new_block.parameters():
            param.requires_grad = True
        
        for param in self.model.fc.parameters():
            param.requires_grad = True

    def forward(self, x : torch.Tensor):
        x = self.model.conv1(x)
        x = self.model.bn1(x)
        x = self.model.relu(x)
        x = self.model.maxpool(x)

        x = self.model.layer1(x)
        x = self.model.layer2(x)
        x = self.model.layer3(x)
        x = self.model.layer4(x)
        x = self.model.new_block(x)
        x = self.model.avgpool(x)
        x = torch.flatten(x, 1)
        x = self.model.fc(x)

        return x

from torchvision.models import inception_v3
from torchvision.models.inception import InceptionAux

class INCEPTION_V3(nn.Module):
    def __init__(self, num_classes: int) -> None:
        super(INCEPTION_V3, self).__init__()
        self.model = inception_v3(weights='Inception_V3_Weights.IMAGENET1K_V1')
        # self.model.aux_logits = False

        self.model.fc = nn.Linear(2048, num_classes)
        self.model.AuxLogits = nn.Sequential(
            nn.Conv2d(in_channels=768, out_channels=64, kernel_size=3, padding=1),
            nn.BatchNorm2d(num_features=64),
            nn.ReLU(inplace=True),
            nn.Conv2d(in_channels=64, out_channels=64, kernel_size=3, padding=1),
            nn.BatchNorm2d(num_features=64),
            nn.ReLU(inplace=True),
            nn.Flatten(),
            nn.Linear(9216, num_classes)
        )

        for param in self.model.AuxLogits.parameters():
            param.requires_grad = True

        for param in self.model.fc.parameters():
            param.requires_grad = True

    def forward_with_aux(self, input):
        out, aux = self.model._forward(input)
        return out, aux

    def forward(self, input):
        out, _ = self.model._forward(input)
        return out


class INCEPTION_V3_PART(nn.Module):
    def __init__(self, num_classes: int) -> None:
        super(INCEPTION_V3_PART, self).__init__()
        self.model = inception_v3(weights='Inception_V3_Weights.IMAGENET1K_V1')
        for param in self.model.parameters():
            param.requires_grad = False

        self.model.fc = nn.Linear(2048, num_classes)
        self.model.AuxLogits = nn.Sequential(
            nn.Conv2d(in_channels=768, out_channels=64, kernel_size=3, padding=1),
            nn.BatchNorm2d(num_features=64),
            nn.ReLU(inplace=True),
            nn.Conv2d(in_channels=64, out_channels=64, kernel_size=3, padding=1),
            nn.BatchNorm2d(num_features=64),
            nn.ReLU(inplace=True),
            nn.Flatten(),
            nn.Linear(9216, num_classes)
        )
        # first 3 layers
        for param in self.model.Conv2d_1a_3x3.parameters():
            param.requires_grad = True
        for param in self.model.Conv2d_2a_3x3.parameters():
            param.requires_grad = True
        for param in self.model.Conv2d_2b_3x3.parameters():
            param.requires_grad = True

        # 3 layers before aux loss 
        for param in self.model.Mixed_6c.parameters():
            param.requires_grad = True
        for param in self.model.Mixed_6d.parameters():
            param.requires_grad = True
        for param in self.model.Mixed_6e.parameters():
            param.requires_grad = True

        # 3 layers before output
        for param in self.model.Mixed_7a.parameters():
            param.requires_grad = True
        for param in self.model.Mixed_7b.parameters():
            param.requires_grad = True
        for param in self.model.Mixed_7c.parameters():
            param.requires_grad = True

    def forward_with_aux(self, input):
        out, aux = self.model._forward(input)
        return out, aux

    def forward(self, input):
        out, _ = self.model._forward(input)
        return out

from torchvision.ops import Permute
from functools import partial

class SWIN_V2_B(nn.Module):
    def __init__(self, num_classes: int):
        super(SWIN_V2_B, self).__init__()
        self.model = models.swin_v2_b(weights='Swin_V2_B_Weights.IMAGENET1K_V1')
        for param in self.model.parameters():
            param.requires_grad = False
        self.model.head = nn.Linear(1024, num_classes)
        for param in self.model.head.parameters():
            param.requires_grad = True

    def forward(self, input):
        return self.model.forward(input)


class SWIN_V2_B_SEVERAL_LAST(nn.Module):
    def __init__(self, num_classes: int):
        super(SWIN_V2_B_SEVERAL_LAST, self).__init__()
        self.model = models.swin_v2_b(weights='Swin_V2_B_Weights.IMAGENET1K_V1')
        for param in self.model.parameters():
            param.requires_grad = False
    
            
        self.model.head = nn.Linear(1024, num_classes)
        for param in self.model.head.parameters():
            param.requires_grad = True
        for param in self.model.features[7].parameters():
            param.requires_grad = True

    def forward(self, input):
        return self.model.forward(input)

class VIT(nn.Module):
    def __init__(self, num_classes: int):
        super(VIT, self).__init__()
        self.model = models.vit_b_16(weights='ViT_B_16_Weights.IMAGENET1K_V1')
        for param in self.model.parameters():
            param.requires_grad = False
        self.model.heads = nn.Linear(768, num_classes)
        for param in self.model.heads.parameters():
            param.requires_grad = True
    
    def forward(self, input):
        return self.model.forward(input)

class VIT_SEVERAL_LAST(nn.Module):
    def __init__(self, num_classes: int):
        super(VIT_SEVERAL_LAST, self).__init__()
        self.model = models.vit_b_16(weights='ViT_B_16_Weights.IMAGENET1K_V1')
        for param in self.model.parameters():
            param.requires_grad = False
        self.model.heads = nn.Linear(768, num_classes)
        for param in self.model.encoder.layers.encoder_layer_11.parameters():
            param.requires_grad = True
        for param in self.model.heads.parameters():
            param.requires_grad = True
    
    def forward(self, input):
        return self.model.forward(input)
In[]:
def train_and_evaluate(model: nn.Module, train_loader, val_loader, milestones, num_epochs=NUM_EPOCHS, learning_rate=LEARNING_RATE, ):
    optimizer = torch.optim.Adam(model.parameters(), lr=learning_rate)
    criterion = nn.CrossEntropyLoss()
    scheduler = optim.lr_scheduler.MultiStepLR(optimizer, milestones=milestones, gamma=0.1)
    val_f1_stat = []
    best_f1 = 0
    for epoch in range(1, num_epochs + 1):
        model.train()
        start = time()
        for images, labels in train_loader:
            images, labels = images.to(device), labels.to(device)
            optimizer.zero_grad()
            if type(model) is INCEPTION_V3 or type(model) is INCEPTION_V3_PART:
                outputs, aux_out = model.forward_with_aux(images)
                loss = criterion(outputs, labels) + 0.5 * criterion(aux_out, labels)
                loss.backward()
            else:
                outputs = model(images)
                loss = criterion(outputs, labels)
                loss.backward()
                
            optimizer.step()
        end = time()
        val_f1 = []
        model.eval()
        with torch.no_grad():
            for images, labels in val_loader:
                images, labels = images.to(device), labels.to(device)
                outputs = model(images)
                _, preds = torch.max(outputs, 1)
                f1 = f1_score(labels.cpu(), preds.cpu(), average='macro')
                val_f1.append(f1)
            val_f1 = sum(val_f1) / len(val_f1)
        if val_f1 > best_f1:
            best_f1 = val_f1
            torch.save(model.state_dict(), f'best_f1_{type(model).__qualname__}.pth')
            print(f"Saved new best model with F1: {best_f1:.2f}")
        val_f1_stat.append(val_f1)
        print(f'Epoch {epoch}: Train time {(end - start):.2f} s, '
            f'Validation F1 {val_f1:.2f}')
        scheduler.step()
    return val_f1_stat

test_f1_stat = {}
In[14]:
def run(model : nn.Module, num_epochs=NUM_EPOCHS, milestones=[20,30]):
    model = model.to(device)
    val_f1_stat = train_and_evaluate(model, train_loader, val_loader, num_epochs=num_epochs, milestones=milestones)
    with torch.no_grad():
        test_f1 = []
        for images, labels in test_loader:
            images, labels = images.to(device), labels.to(device)
            outputs = model(images)
            _, preds = torch.max(outputs, 1)
            f1 = f1_score(labels.cpu(), preds.cpu(), average='macro')
            test_f1.append(f1)
        latest_train_test_f1 = sum(test_f1) / len(test_f1)

        test_f1 = []
        model.load_state_dict(torch.load(f'best_f1_{type(model).__qualname__}.pth', weights_only=True))
        for images, labels in test_loader:
            images, labels = images.to(device), labels.to(device)
            outputs = model(images)
            _, preds = torch.max(outputs, 1)
            f1 = f1_score(labels.cpu(), preds.cpu(), average='macro')
            test_f1.append(f1)
        best_test_f1 = sum(test_f1) / len(test_f1)
    print(f"Latest train F1 Test: {latest_train_test_f1:.2f}, Best F1 Test: {best_test_f1:.2f}")
    plt.plot(range(num_epochs), val_f1_stat, marker="o")
    plt.title("Validation F1")
    plt.xlabel("epoch")
    plt.ylabel("F1 score")
    plt.show()
    test_f1_stat[type(model).__qualname__] = max(latest_train_test_f1, best_test_f1)
